A4.text: Melbourne ( MEL-bərn, locally [ˈmæɫbən] ; Boonwurrung/Woiwurrung: Narrm or Naarm) is the capital and most populous city of the Australian state of Victoria

A5.text: Declared a city by Queen Victoria in 1847, it became the capital of the newly separated Colony of Victoria in 1851.
